    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i hear the \"innovation\" thing a lot but for a small shop that just wants to stay afloat, won't these costs just be a straight up killer? feels like the benefits are mostly theoretical while the bills are very real for local biz. can u look into how much these compliance costs actually hit the bottom line compared to the actual environmental gains?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
